Product Id: 2009 data - Total household population aged 6 to 79, except those meeting the exclusion criteria (see the Canadian Health Measures Survey (CHMS) Data User Guide: Cycle 1). Data collected between March 2007 and February 2009.

2011 data - Total household population aged 3 to 79, except those meeting the exclusion criteria (see the Canadian Health Measures Survey (CHMS) Data User Guide: Cycle 2). Data collected between August 2009 and November 2011.

2013 data - Total household population aged 3 to 79, except those meeting the exclusion criteria (see the Canadian Health Measures Survey (CHMS) Data User Guide: Cycle 3). Data collected between January 2012 and December 2013.

2015 data - Total household population aged 3 to 79, except those meeting the exclusion criteria (see the Canadian Health Measures Survey (CHMS) Data User Guide: Cycle 4). Data collected between January 2014 and December 2015.

2017 data - Total household population aged 3 to 79, except those meeting the exclusion criteria (see the Canadian Health Measures Survey (CHMS) Data User Guide: Cycle 5). Data collected between January 2016 and December 2017.

2019 data - Total household population aged 3 to 79, except those meeting the exclusion criteria (see the Canadian Health Measures Survey (CHMS) Data User Guide: Cycle 6). Data collected between January 2018 and December 2019.

Accelerometry data for 3-5 year old children was collected in 60 second epochs (defined movement intervals) for the 2011 reference period and in 15 second epochs for all other reference periods. The data cannot be compared between reference periods as there are differences in the amount of physical activity time captured using the different epoch times. Thresholds for moderate to vigorous activity for the 2011 reference period were updated to be consistent with 2013 and 2015 (update made in 2016).
The sample size for 3 to 5 year olds produces reliable national estimates for both sexes combined only.
